      <varlistentry><term>help function for EMD  :</term>
   <listitem>
    <para><link linkend="zero_crossings">zero_crossings</link> finds zero-crossings</para>
      <para><link linkend="peaks">peaks</link> finds peaks (local maxima)</para>
   <para><link linkend="local_peaks">local_peaks</link>  finds local extrema </para>
        <para><link linkend="io">io</link> computes the index of orthogonality</para>
     </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   
   <varlistentry><term>visualization of EMD  :</term>
   <listitem>
    <para><link linkend="disp_hhs">disp_hhs</link>  display Hilbert-Huang spectrum</para>
   <para><link linkend="emd_visu">emd_visu</link> visualization of EMD and partial reconstructions</para>
 <para><link linkend="toimage">toimage</link> transforms a spectrum made of 1D functions in an 2D image</para>
 <para><link linkend="hhspectrum">hhspectrum</link> compute Hilbert-Huang spectrum</para>
 <para><link linkend="cemd_visu">cemd_visu</link>visualization of bivariate/complex EMD</para>
  <para><link linkend="cemd_disp">cemd_disp</link> displays complex envelope curves and the corresponding tube envelope</para>
 <para><link linkend="plotc">plotc</link>  plots a complex signal in 2D projection with variable projection angle.</para>
 <para><link linkend="plot3c">plot3c</link> plots a complex signal in 3D</para>
 <para><link linkend="cenvelope">cenvelope</link>  computes envelope curves for bivariate EMD</para>
  <para><link linkend="emd_reconstruct">emd_reconstruct</link>  partial reconstructions (fine to coarse and coarse to fine) for real and complex data.</para>
   </listitem>
